.TH arctgz 7 "2026-07-19" "arctgz 0.6.0" "Miscellaneous Information Manual"
.SH NAME
arctgz \- safety-first project lifecycle library for the arctgz archive format
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
\fBuse arctgz::{\fP
\fB    init, load_config, save_config,\fP
\fB    compile, extract, verify,\fP
\fB    load_recipe, extract_recipe, execute_recipe,\fP
\fB    ArctgzConfig, ArctgzManifest, FileEntry,\fP
\fB    ArctgzRecipe, RecipeStep, Compression, ArctgzError\fP
\fB};\fP
\fBuse std::path::Path;\fP

\fBfn init(project_path: &Path, force: bool) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;\fP
\fBfn load_config(project_path: &Path) -> Result<ArctgzConfig, ArctgzError>;\fP
\fBfn save_config(project_path: &Path, config: &ArctgzConfig) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;\fP
\fBfn compile(\fP
\fB    project_path: &Path,\fP
\fB    output_dir: Option<&Path>,\fP
\fB    force: bool\fP
\fB) -> Result<PathBuf, ArctgzError>;\fP
\fBfn extract(\fP
\fB    archive_path: &Path,\fP
\fB    output_dir: &Path,\fP
\fB    force: bool\fP
\fB) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;\fP
\fBfn verify(archive_path: &Path) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;\fP
\fBfn load_recipe(project_path: &Path) -> Result<Option<ArctgzRecipe>, ArctgzError>;\fP
\fBfn extract_recipe(archive_path: &Path) -> Result<ArctgzRecipe, ArctgzError>;\fP
\fBfn execute_recipe(\fP
\fB    output_dir: &Path,\fP
\fB    recipe: &ArctgzRecipe,\fP
\fB    force: bool\fP
\fB) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;\fP

\fBstruct ArctgzConfig {\fP
    \fBpub name:        String,\fP
    \fBpub version:     String,\fP
    \fBpub include:     Vec<String>,\fP
    \fBpub compression: Compression,\fP
\fB}\fP

\fBstruct ArctgzManifest {\fP
    \fBpub name:        String,\fP
    \fBpub version:     String,\fP
    \fBpub created:     DateTime<Utc>,\fP
    \fBpub compression: Compression,\fP
    \fBpub files:       BTreeMap<String, FileEntry>,\fP
\fB}\fP

\fBstruct FileEntry {\fP
    \fBpub size:   u64,\fP
    \fBpub sha512: String,\fP
\fB}\fP

\fBstruct ArctgzRecipe {\fP
    \fBpub name:    String,\fP
    \fBpub version: String,\fP
    \fBpub steps:   Vec<RecipeStep>,\fP
\fB}\fP

\fBenum RecipeStep {\fP
    \fBCopy   { from: String, to: String },\fP
    \fBMkDir  { path: String },\fP
    \fBChmod  { path: String, mode: String },\fP
    \fBRemove { path: String },\fP
\fB}\fP

\fBenum Compression {\fP
    \fBGzip,\fP
    \fBZstd,\fP
\fB}\fP

\fBenum ArctgzError { ... }\fP
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The arctgz library provides a safe, cross-platform API for the full lifecycle of an arctgz project: scaffolding, configuration, compilation into a compressed and integrity-verified archive, verified extraction, standalone verification, and post-extraction recipe execution.
.PP
All operations enforce strict path confinement, validate metadata before touching the filesystem, and use atomic file operations to prevent corruption and TOCTOU (time-of-check to time-of-use) races.
.PP
The core functionality includes:
.IP \(bu 2
\fBinit\fP() \(en scaffold a new project directory with a default configuration and an empty resource folder.
.IP \(bu
\fBload_config\fP() / \fBsave_config\fP() \(en read and write validated project configuration.
.IP \(bu
\fBcompile\fP() \(en create a compressed archive (gzip or zstd) with SHA-512 hashes and a manifest; supports parallel hashing via rayon.
.IP \(bu
\fBextract\fP() \(en unpack an archive with full integrity checks and path traversal prevention.
.IP \(bu
\fBverify\fP() \(en check archive integrity without writing files.
.IP \(bu
\fBload_recipe\fP() / \fBextract_recipe\fP() / \fBexecute_recipe\fP() \(en manage and execute post-extraction recipes (copy, mkdir, chmod, remove).
.PP
All paths are resolved with \fBstd::fs::canonicalize\fP() (equivalent to \fBrealpath\fP(3)), so symbolic links are followed during the home-directory confinement check.
The library is fully tested on Linux, macOS, and Windows.
.SH INSTALLATION
This man page can be installed system-wide using the provided installer script:
.PP
.nf
\fBcurl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mroczect/arctgz/master/install-manpage.sh | bash\fP
.fi
.PP
The script places \fBarctgz.7\fP into \fB/usr/local/share/man/man7/\fP and updates the man database.
To uninstall, run:
.PP
.nf
\fBcurl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mroczect/arctgz/master/install-manpage.sh | bash -s -- uninstall\fP
.fi
.SH FUNCTIONS
.TP
\fBinit\fP(\fIproject_path\fP, \fIforce\fP)
.RS
Initialises a new arctgz project at \fIproject_path\fP.
.PP
Arguments:
.RS
.TP
\fIproject_path\fP
A reference to a \fBstd::path::Path\fP.
The path must not be empty and must reside (after canonicalisation) under the current user's home directory.
If the path does not exist, it will be created; otherwise it must be a directory.
.TP
\fIforce\fP
If \fBtrue\fP, skip the non-empty directory check.
However, an existing \fBarctgz.init\fP file will still cause an \fBAlreadyInitialized\fP error.
.RE
.PP
Return value:
.RS
\fBOk(())\fP on success, or an \fBArctgzError\fP describing the failure.
.RE
.PP
Side effects (only after all safety checks pass):
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Creates the project directory (and parents, if needed).
.IP \(bu
Creates the \fBinclude/\fP subdirectory.
.IP \(bu
Writes a default \fBarctgz.init\fP configuration file atomically (using \fBcreate_new(true)\fP).
The default configuration includes \fB"compression": "gzip"\fP.
.RE
.PP
Security checks (performed before any filesystem modification):
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Home directory confinement \(en the canonicalised project path must start with the canonicalised home directory.
Symlink attacks are neutralised.
.IP \(bu
Path validity \(en rejects empty paths, and rejects existing files (as opposed to directories).
.IP \(bu
Directory emptiness (unless \fBforce\fP is \fBtrue\fP).
.RE
.RE
.TP
\fBload_config\fP(\fIproject_path\fP)
.RS
Reads and validates the \fBarctgz.init\fP file from the given project directory.
.PP
Arguments:
.RS
.TP
\fIproject_path\fP
Path to the project root (must contain an \fBarctgz.init\fP file).
.RE
.PP
Return value:
.RS
\fBOk(ArctgzConfig)\fP if the file exists, contains valid JSON, and passes \fBvalidate()\fP.
On failure, returns an \fBArctgzError\fP variant (\fBConfigNotFound\fP, \fBConfigLoadError\fP, or \fBConfigValidation\fP).
.RE
.RE
.TP
\fBsave_config\fP(\fIproject_path\fP, \fIconfig\fP)
.RS
Writes a validated \fBArctgzConfig\fP back to the project's \fBarctgz.init\fP file atomically.
The operation first writes the JSON to a temporary file (\fBarctgz.tmp\fP) and then renames it over the original.
This prevents corruption if the process crashes mid-write.
.PP
Arguments:
.RS
.TP
\fIproject_path\fP
Path to the project root.
.TP
\fIconfig\fP
An \fBArctgzConfig\fP instance to save.
Must pass \fBvalidate()\fP before saving.
.RE
.PP
Return value:
.RS
\fBOk(())\fP on success, or an \fBArctgzError\fP (\fBConfigValidation\fP, \fBConfigSaveError\fP, or \fBJson\fP).
.RE
.RE
.TP
\fBcompile\fP(\fIproject_path\fP, \fIoutput_dir\fP, \fIforce\fP)
.RS
Compiles the project into an \fB.artgz\fP archive.
.PP
The function:
.IP \(bu 2
Loads the project configuration via \fBload_config\fP().
.IP \(bu
Collects the \fBarctgz.init\fP file and all files listed in the \fBinclude\fP array, recursively adding directories while rejecting symbolic links.
An optional \fBrecipe.json\fP is also included if present.
.IP \(bu
Computes SHA-512 hashes for every file in parallel using \fBrayon\fP.
.IP \(bu
Embeds an \fBArctgzManifest\fP as \fBmanifest.json\fP.
.IP \(bu
Compresses the tar stream with the configured algorithm (\fBCompression::Gzip\fP or \fBCompression::Zstd\fP).
.IP \(bu
Writes the archive atomically via a temporary file and rename.
.PP
Arguments:
.RS
.TP
\fIproject_path\fP
Path to the project root.
.TP
\fIoutput_dir\fP
Optional output directory.
If \fBNone\fP, the archive is placed in \fBproject_path/dist/\fP.
.TP
\fIforce\fP
If \fBtrue\fP, overwrite an existing archive; otherwise fail if the archive already exists.
.RE
.PP
Return value:
.RS
\fBOk(PathBuf)\fP containing the full path to the created archive, or an \fBArctgzError\fP (including \fBIncludeFileNotFound\fP, \fBSymlinkNotAllowed\fP, \fBRecipeInvalid\fP, or \fBIo\fP for an already-existing archive when \fBforce\fP is \fBfalse\fP).
.RE
.PP
Safety:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Symlinks are rejected to prevent reference leaks outside the project.
.IP \(bu
If a \fBrecipe.json\fP is present, it is validated before compilation; invalid recipes cause \fBRecipeInvalid\fP.
.IP \(bu
The entire archive is written atomically; a crash mid-write leaves no partial archive.
.RE
.RE
.TP
\fBextract\fP(\fIarchive_path\fP, \fIoutput_dir\fP, \fIforce\fP)
.RS
Extracts a previously compiled arctgz archive with full integrity verification.
Compression (gzip/zstd) is detected automatically.
.PP
The function:
.IP \(bu 2
Opens and decompresses the archive.
.IP \(bu
Reads the embedded \fBmanifest.json\fP and validates it.
.IP \(bu
Checks each file path using \fBis_safe_archive_path\fP (rejects absolute paths, \fB..\fP, empty strings, and \fB.\fP).
.IP \(bu
Verifies that all files in the manifest are present and vice versa.
.IP \(bu
Hashes each file and compares against the manifest; any mismatch aborts with \fBChecksumMismatch\fP and removes the partially written file.
.IP \(bu
Writes files to \fIoutput_dir\fP, creating subdirectories as needed, and refuses to overwrite existing files unless \fBforce\fP is \fBtrue\fP.
.PP
Arguments:
.RS
.TP
\fIarchive_path\fP
Path to the \fB.artgz\fP archive.
.TP
\fIoutput_dir\fP
Destination directory; will be created if it does not exist.
.TP
\fIforce\fP
If \fBtrue\fP, overwrite existing files; otherwise abort on conflict.
.RE
.PP
Return value:
.RS
\fBOk(())\fP on success, or an \fBArctgzError\fP (\fBManifestNotFound\fP, \fBChecksumMismatch\fP, \fBExtractError\fP for unsafe paths, or \fBIo\fP for file conflicts).
.RE
.RE
.TP
\fBverify\fP(\fIarchive_path\fP)
.RS
Standalone integrity check.
Reads the archive, validates every file's hash and size against the manifest, ensures all manifest entries are present, and checks for unsafe paths.
No files are written.
.PP
Return value:
.RS
\fBOk(())\fP if the archive is valid, or an \fBArctgzError\fP (\fBManifestNotFound\fP, \fBChecksumMismatch\fP for hash or size mismatch, \fBVerifyError\fP for missing/extra files or unsafe paths).
.RE
.RE
.TP
\fBload_recipe\fP(\fIproject_path\fP)
.RS
Loads and validates \fBrecipe.json\fP from a project directory.
Returns \fBOk(None)\fP if the file does not exist.
.RE
.TP
\fBextract_recipe\fP(\fIarchive_path\fP)
.RS
Extracts and validates the embedded \fBrecipe.json\fP from an archive.
Automatically detects compression format (gzip or zstd).
Returns \fBRecipeNotFound\fP if the recipe is missing.
.RE
.TP
\fBexecute_recipe\fP(\fIoutput_dir\fP, \fIrecipe\fP, \fIforce\fP)
.RS
Runs the steps of a recipe inside \fIoutput_dir\fP.
Supported steps:
.RS
.TP
\fBCopy { from, to }\fP
Copy a file or directory.
.TP
\fBMkDir { path }\fP
Create a directory.
.TP
\fBChmod { path, mode }\fP
Set Unix permissions (octal string).
On non-Unix platforms this step returns \fBRecipeExecutionError\fP and halts execution.
.TP
\fBRemove { path }\fP
Delete a file or directory.
.RE
.PP
All recipe paths are validated: absolute paths, \fB..\fP, empty strings, and \fB.\fP are rejected.
When \fBforce\fP is \fBfalse\fP, existing files or directories cause an error.
.PP
Return value:
.RS
\fBOk(())\fP on success, or an \fBArctgzError\fP (\fBRecipeInvalid\fP, \fBRecipeExecutionError\fP).
.RE
.RE
.SH TYPES
.TP
\fBArctgzConfig\fP
Project configuration stored in \fBarctgz.init\fP.
.RS
.TP
\fBname\fP
Project name (alphanumeric, \fB-\fP, \fB_\fP; max 255 chars).
.TP
\fBversion\fP
Semantic version string.
.TP
\fBinclude\fP
List of relative resource paths (max 100 entries, no \fB..\fP or absolute paths).
.TP
\fBcompression\fP
Compression algorithm: \fB"gzip"\fP (default) or \fB"zstd"\fP.
.RE
.PP
The configuration file is JSON with \fB#[serde(deny_unknown_fields)]\fP; unknown keys cause a deserialisation error.
.TP
\fBArctgzManifest\fP
Embedded in every archive as \fBmanifest.json\fP.
.RS
.TP
\fBname\fP, \fBversion\fP
Copied from config.
.TP
\fBcreated\fP
UTC timestamp of compilation.
.TP
\fBcompression\fP
Algorithm used for this archive.
.TP
\fBfiles\fP
\fBBTreeMap\fP from archive paths to \fBFileEntry\fP.
.RE
.TP
\fBFileEntry\fP
Metadata for one file: \fBsize\fP (u64) and \fBsha512\fP hex string.
.TP
\fBArctgzRecipe\fP
Describes post-extraction actions.
.RS
.TP
\fBname\fP, \fBversion\fP
Recipe identity.
.TP
\fBsteps\fP
Ordered list of \fBRecipeStep\fP.
.RE
.TP
\fBRecipeStep\fP
Enum with \fBCopy\fP, \fBMkDir\fP, \fBChmod\fP, \fBRemove\fP.
.TP
\fBCompression\fP
Enum: \fBGzip\fP (default), \fBZstd\fP.
.TP
\fBArctgzError\fP
All failure variants, including:
.RS
.TP
\fBRecipeNotFound\fP
Recipe not found in archive.
.TP
\fBRecipeInvalid\fP
Recipe validation failed.
.TP
\fBRecipeExecutionError\fP
Recipe step could not be performed.
.TP
\fBVerifyError\fP
Verification failed (missing file, size mismatch, unsafe path, etc.).
.RE
.SH EXAMPLE
.SS Initialising a project with zstd compression
.nf
\fBuse arctgz::{init, load_config, save_config, Compression};\fP

\fBfn main() -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {\fP
    \fBlet project = Path::new("./my-project");\fP
    \fBinit(project, false)?;\fP
    \fBlet mut cfg = load_config(project)?;\fP
    \fBcfg.compression = Compression::Zstd;\fP
    \fBsave_config(project, &cfg)?;\fP
    \fBOk(())\fP
\fB}\fP
.fi
.SS Compile, verify, and extract with a recipe
.nf
\fBuse arctgz::{compile, verify, extract, execute_recipe, extract_recipe};\fP

\fBfn build_and_deploy(project: &Path) -> Result<(), arctgz::ArctgzError> {\fP
    \fBlet archive = compile(project, None, false)?;\fP
    \fBverify(&archive)?;\fP
    \fBlet out_dir = Path::new("/tmp/deploy");\fP
    \fBextract(&archive, out_dir, true)?;\fP
    \fBlet recipe = extract_recipe(&archive)?;\fP
    \fBexecute_recipe(out_dir, &recipe, true)?;\fP
    \fBOk(())\fP
\fB}\fP
.fi
.SS Example recipe.json
.nf
{
  "name": "setup",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "steps": [
    { "action": "mkdir", "path": "logs" },
    { "action": "copy", "from": "default.cfg", "to": "config.cfg" },
    { "action": "chmod", "path": "bin/app", "mode": "755" },
    { "action": "remove", "path": "temp.txt" }
  ]
}
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
\fBarctgz.init\fP
Project configuration (JSON).
The file is strictly validated; unknown fields cause an error.
Written atomically by \fBinit\fP() and \fBsave_config\fP().
.TP
\fBinclude/\fP
Resource directory.
.TP
\fBdist/<name>-<version>.artgz\fP
Default archive output (gzip or zstd).
.TP
\fBrecipe.json\fP (optional)
Post-extraction recipe embedded into the archive.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\fBHOME\fP (Unix) / \fBUSERPROFILE\fP (Windows)
The library obtains the current user's home directory through the \fBdirs\fP crate.
On Unix, the \fBHOME\fP variable is used; on Windows, \fBUSERPROFILE\fP.
If the appropriate variable is not set, a platform-specific fallback is attempted.
If no home directory can be determined, \fBinit\fP() will fail with \fBPathNotAllowed\fP for any path (even relative ones) because confinement cannot be verified.
.SH SECURITY
.IP \(bu 2
Path confinement: only paths inside the canonicalised home directory are allowed for initialisation.
Symlink traversal is fully mitigated by canonicalising both the project path and the home directory.
.IP \(bu
No side effects before validation: \fBinit\fP() resolves the path and performs all security checks before creating any directories.
Thus, even a failed call with a path outside the home directory will not leave unwanted directories on disk.
.IP \(bu
Atomic writes: the use of \fBcreate_new(true)\fP for \fBinit\fP(), and temp file + rename for \fBsave_config\fP() and \fBcompile\fP(), ensure the target file is never left in an incomplete state.
.IP \(bu
Archive integrity: every file in the archive is hashed with SHA-512.
The manifest is embedded and verified during extraction and verification; any hash or size mismatch aborts with \fBChecksumMismatch\fP.
.IP \(bu
Path traversal prevention: \fBextract\fP() and \fBverify\fP() reject archive paths that are absolute, contain \fB..\fP, are empty, or equal \fB.\fP.
The same validation applies to recipe paths.
.IP \(bu
Symlink rejection: \fBcompile\fP() refuses to include symbolic links, ensuring archives contain only regular files and directories.
.IP \(bu
Input validation: configuration and recipe fields are strictly validated.
Unknown JSON keys are rejected, preventing accidental or malicious settings from entering the project metadata.
.SH NOTES
The library is intended to be used as a building block for higher-level tools.
It does not impose any locking mechanism; concurrent operations on the same project directory may lead to races.
However, each individual write operation (config save, archive creation) is atomic, so partial corruption is avoided even under concurrent access.
Users should serialise access when multiple processes or threads operate on the same project.
.SH VERSION
arctgz 0.6.0 \(en introduces robust manifest reading via \fBread_manifest\fP, improved path safety checks (\fBis_safe_archive_path\fP), and corrects the behaviour of \fBChmod\fP on non-Unix platforms to return an error instead of silently doing nothing.
